commit.message: Prepared 1.1.0 release
Support file objects as content. Fixes #56 (#57)
Prepare for a release
Documented the low level bewit API
Fix up changelog, fix sphinx links
Match python 3 version that is tested in tox
More README
Freshend up the docs and package metadata
Allow Receiver to accept requests if both the hash and payload are missing (#49)
Change default values of `content`, `content_type` for hash checks (#45)
Add Python 3.6 to tox/Travis env list (#44)

Merge pull request #33 from megacool/explicit-regex

Use explicit matching for a-z, A-Z and 0-9

Use explicit matching for a-z, A-Z, 0-9 and _

This also drops the re.LOCALE flag, which would cause whatever
characters defined by the current locale as alphanumeric to be
accepted as valid header values, thus causing potential differences
between deployments based on locale settings.

Closes #32
